---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import SampleComponent from "@components/SampleComponent.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import AstroLogo from "@assets/images/astro-logo-light-gradient.png";
import { Content as SampleMarkdown } from "@content/sample-markdown.md";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<Layout title="Astro Starter">
  <div class="intro">
    <h1>Since the dawn of man...</h1>
    <h1>There has been one question that has persisted above all else...</h1>
    <h1>logo</h1>
  </div>

  <section class="bigpic1">
      <div class ="bigpic-text">
    <p>fat dookie</p>
      </div>
    <img src="the goat.jpg" alt="VespaPug">
  </section>

<section class="textpic">
      <div class="textpic-text">
  <p>Starting off with Man’s Best Friend: The Dog. Dogs are known for loving one thing above all else: sticking their head out the window. With this in mind there is only one option I view as optimal… <strong>The Motorcycle</strong>, the motorcycle would allow these dogs to be as free as they want while being perfect for the size of your above average mutt.</p>
      </div>
    <img src="the goat.jpg" alt="VespaPug">
  </section>
<div class ="text">
  <p><em>But then this begs the question. What of our smaller pals?<br>Pugs, chihuahuas, pomeranians, dachshunds, etc.,<br> What would they ride? Well to me, the answer is quite simple…</em>
</p>
</div>


<section class="textpic-r">
  <div class="textpic-text">
  <p>These small dogs would drive vespas, the slower, tinier sibling to the motorcycle. This all-italian classic would let our tiny puppy pals drive in piece, leaving nothing but a good time in their wake.</p>
</div>
  <img src="the goat.jpg" alt="VespaPug">
</section>

<section class="bigpic">
      <div class ="bigpic-text">
    <p>CATS</p>
      </div>
    <img src="catcover.jpg" alt="Cat Driving">
  </section>

  <section class="textpic-r">
      <div class="textpic-text">
  <p>Up next on the list, is the cat. These anti-social weirdos would 1000% drive <strong>Two Seaters</strong>. I believe this is the case for a few reasons.<br>
First and foremost: cats would drive cars, no doubt about it, they wouldn’t want to bother with the wreckless lifestyle of the dog. Instead, they’d prefer to sit in silence.</p>
      </div> 
      <img src="the goat.jpg" alt="VespaPug">
  </section>
      
      <section class="textpic">
      <div class="textpic-text">
  <p>The second, and more important reason, is their own self absorbed nature, they wouldn’t want to share their car with more than one person at a time (if that). Meaning that the two seater is the perfect match for these hairballs.</p>
      </div>
    <img src="the goat.jpg" alt="VespaPug">
  </section>

<section class="bigpic">
      <div class ="bigpic-text">
    <p>BEARS</p>
      </div>
    <img src="bearvan.jpg" alt="Bear Driving">
  </section>

  <section class="textpic-r">
      <div class="textpic-text">
  <p>The third and most simple one on our list: Bears. Bears are big, so they need a big vehicle. They would drive trucks.</p>
      </div> 
      <img src="the goat.jpg" alt="VespaPug">
  </section>

<div class="s-footer">
  <p>footer</p>
</div>

</Layout>

